comment: Jackson (DET) is in a legal guarding position on James' (CLE) drive.
Jackson (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he contests James' (CLE) shot in the lane.
Drummond (DET) is in the paint within an arm's distance of Mozgov (CLE) and considered actively guarding, which suspends the defensive three seconds count.
James (CLE) throws the pass into the backcourt and Williams (CLE) is the first player to touch the ball.
Dellavedova (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and contact is created by Jackson (DET) as he begins his drive.
Dellavedova (CLE) sets the screen on Morris (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ilyasova (DET) and Thompson (CLE) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Dellavedova (CLE) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
After communicating with the Replay Center, Dellavedova (ACLE) was assessed a common foul as it was determined the foul did not meet the criteria of a flagrant foul.
Thompson (CLE) sets the screen on Morris (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Williams (CLE) makes contact with Jackson's (DET) arm as he goes for the steal.
Thompson (CLE) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Smith (CLE) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Drummond (DET) was upheld.
